sorcer.service.modeling

Interface Getter<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Arg, Call, EvaluationComponent, Filtration, Request, java.io.Serializable, Service, SupportComponent

    public interface Getter<T>
extends Filtration, EvaluationComponent, SupportComponent
    A getter is a generic agent that returns a value calculated in many different ways. A getter may evaluate provided arguments and return a calculated value by itself or retrieve value from a data repository. Alternatively a getter may use a target as an independent agent at which the getting operation is aimed (the third party service) to obtain the requested value or finally as a filter that can filter out the value from the provided target.
